<div class="about-content">
    <p>Hi!</p>

    <p>I'm David and I like to take pictures in my free time. I work as a DevOps Engineer in Switzerland. I like to spend as much Time outside as possible. The photographs on this site were taken with a mixture of cameras. Most of them analog. Currently, I use the following kit:</p>

    <ul>
    <li>Chamonix F2 4x5 with the following lenses: Fujinon 90mm, Nikkor 180mm, Nikkor 360mm</li>
    <li>Bronica SQ</li>
    <li>Olympus XA</li>
    <li>Fujifilm X100F</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Most of photographs are taken around Switzerland. A few are from Scandinavia or further away (From me at least :P).</p>

    <p>A few books I like for various reasons, in no particular order:</p>

    <ul>
    <li>The Lord of the Rings, J.R.R. Tolkien</li>
    <li>Wie der Berg zu seinem Namen kam, Andrea Schorta</li>
    <li>Dune, Frank Herbert</li>
    <li>The Complete Robot, Isaac Asimov</li>
    <li>Die Zürcher Bibel</li>
    <li>The Wheel of Time Series, Robert Jordan</li>
    <li>Utvandrarna, Vilhelm Moberg</li>
    </ul>
</div>
